Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.10,0:00:04.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,本期Primal Space视频由CuriosityStream赞助
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.10,0:00:04.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,This episode of Primal Space is supported by CuriosityStream.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:04.05,0:00:10.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,前往curiositystream.com/primalspace即可免费观看上千部纪录片
Dialogue: 2,0:00:04.05,0:00:10.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,Watch thousands of documentaries for free by visiting curiositystream.com/primalspace
Dialogue: 1,0:00:10.65,0:00:16.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,2024年 太空叉打算送首批人类踏上前往火星的为期半年的征程
Dialogue: 2,0:00:10.65,0:00:16.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,In 2024, SpaceX aims to send the first humans on a 6 month trip to Mars.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.13,0:00:22.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,这趟旅程将是马一龙的“让人类成为多星球物种”目标的第一步
Dialogue: 2,0:00:17.13,0:00:22.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,This journey will be the very beginning of Elon Musk's goal to make life a multiplanetary species.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:23.04,0:00:28.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,为了达到这个目标 太空叉需要建立人类第一个火星基地
Dialogue: 2,0:00:23.04,0:00:28.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,In order to achieve this, SpaceX will need to establish the first Martian base and -
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.33,0:00:30.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,并慢慢变成首个火星城市
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.33,0:00:30.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,over time - the first Martian city.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:31.10,0:00:35.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,利用Starship火箭 数千人将能够前往火星旅行
Dialogue: 2,0:00:31.10,0:00:35.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,Using their Starship rocket, thousands of people will be able to travel to Mars
Dialogue: 1,0:00:35.69,0:00:40.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,并为建立首个地球外人类文明打下基础
Dialogue: 2,0:00:35.69,0:00:40.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,and lay the foundation for the first human civilization outside of Earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:40.73,0:00:43.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,但首批宇航员将如何在火星建立基地？
Dialogue: 2,0:00:40.73,0:00:43.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,But how will the first astronauts establish a base on Mars?
Dialogue: 1,0:00:44.13,0:00:45.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们将遵循怎样的法律？
Dialogue: 2,0:00:44.13,0:00:45.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,And what laws will they follow?
Dialogue: 1,0:00:46.26,0:00:51.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,本期视频 我们将了解在火星建立一个自给自足的城市都需要什么
Dialogue: 2,0:00:46.26,0:00:51.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,In this video, we're going to look at what it will take to build a self-sustaining city on Mars.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:51.80,0:00:55.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们还将了解火星居民将如何建构他们自己的法律体系
Dialogue: 2,0:00:51.80,0:00:55.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're also going to look at how Martians will form their own laws
Dialogue: 1,0:00:55.13,0:00:58.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,来让他们发展成繁荣的城市
Dialogue: 2,0:00:55.13,0:00:58.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,in order to grow the first settlements into thriving cities.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:59.34,0:01:03.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,当首批宇航员抵达火星时 他们需要一个住的地方
Dialogue: 2,0:00:59.34,0:01:03.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,When the first astronauts arrive on Mars they will need a place to stay.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:03.63,0:01:07.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为火星表面受到的辐射比地球大得多
Dialogue: 2,0:01:03.63,0:01:07.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since the Martian surface is exposed to much more radiation than Earth,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:07.30,0:01:11.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,首个火星居住舱很可能会建于地下
Dialogue: 2,0:01:07.30,0:01:11.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,the first Martian habitats will most likely be built underground.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:11.62,0:01:16.34,辉中,,0,0,0,,更先进的居住舱可以建在地上 外壳用厚厚的水层来抵御大多数辐射
Dialogue: 2,0:01:11.62,0:01:16.34,辉英,,0,0,0,,More sophisticated habitats could be built above land with a thick layer of water to
Dialogue: 1,0:01:16.35,0:01:18.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,更先进的居住舱可以建在地上 外壳用厚厚的水层来抵御大多数辐射
Dialogue: 2,0:01:16.35,0:01:18.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,absorb most of the radiation.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:18.28,0:01:22.69,辉中,,0,0,0,,然而 运输大量的水和建造居住舱的材料价格极其昂贵
Dialogue: 2,0:01:18.28,0:01:22.69,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, transporting the enormous amounts of water and materials needed to build these
Dialogue: 1,0:01:22.69,0:01:25.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,然而 运输大量的水和建造居住舱的材料价格极其昂贵
Dialogue: 2,0:01:22.69,0:01:25.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,habitats would be extremely expensive.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:25.78,0:01:29.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,首批火星居民想要发展壮大成城市
Dialogue: 2,0:01:25.78,0:01:29.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,If the first Martian habitats are to grow into large cities,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:29.17,0:01:32.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们就必须在火星就地取材
Dialogue: 2,0:01:29.17,0:01:32.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,the settlers will need to use the local materials found on Mars.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:33.17,0:01:36.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,幸运的是 火星有大量有用的资源
Dialogue: 2,0:01:33.17,0:01:36.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,Luckily, Mars has a large amount of useful resources.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:37.18,0:01:41.58,辉中,,0,0,0,,星球表面有铁 镁和铝等金属
Dialogue: 2,0:01:37.18,0:01:41.58,辉英,,0,0,0,,The surface of the planet contains metals like iron, magnesium and aluminium,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:41.63,0:01:43.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,还可以从太阳获取电能
Dialogue: 2,0:01:41.63,0:01:43.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,while power could be harnessed from the sun.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:44.11,0:01:46.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,星球大气中存在氧气
Dialogue: 2,0:01:44.11,0:01:46.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,Oxygen is present in the planet's atmosphere
Dialogue: 1,0:01:46.84,0:01:50.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,星球表面下还有冰 可以提供所需的水资源
Dialogue: 2,0:01:46.84,0:01:50.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,and ice buried beneath the surface could supply all the water needed.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:51.28,0:01:56.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,但当宇航员开始开采这些材料的时候 开采出来的东西归谁？
Dialogue: 2,0:01:51.28,0:01:56.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,But once the Martians begin mining these materials for their own use, who owns them?
Dialogue: 1,0:01:56.65,0:02:02.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,1967年 美国 英国和苏联都签署了《外层空间条约》
Dialogue: 2,0:01:56.65,0:02:02.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,In 1967, the US, UK and the Soviet Union all signed the Outer Space Treaty.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:03.20,0:02:08.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,条约规定任何国家不得将太空或某天体据为己有
Dialogue: 2,0:02:03.20,0:02:08.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,The treaty claims that no nation can claim ownership of space or a celestial body.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:08.34,0:02:14.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以定居火星的人唯一要做的就是建立并执行规则了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:08.34,0:02:14.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,It would therefore be the sole responsibility of the Martian settlers to establish and enforce rules.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:14.74,0:02:20.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,但历史告诉我们 建立新的殖民地一点都不简单
Dialogue: 2,0:02:14.74,0:02:20.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,But if history tells us anything, it's that creating a new colony is anything but easy.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:21.26,0:02:26.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,1607年5月 104人登上詹姆士镇
Dialogue: 2,0:02:21.26,0:02:26.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,In May 1607, 104 people set foot on to Jamestown.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:26.38,0:02:30.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,但到了一月 就只剩38人存活了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:26.38,0:02:30.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,By January, only 38 of these original settlers were still alive.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:30.96,0:02:33.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们中许多人死于疾病与饥荒
Dialogue: 2,0:02:30.96,0:02:33.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,Many of these people died from disease and famine,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:33.82,0:02:37.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,还有人死于不干净的水源和部落冲突
Dialogue: 2,0:02:33.82,0:02:37.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,while others passed away from toxic water and tribal warfare.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:38.33,0:02:40.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果在地球建立新殖民地就已经很困难
Dialogue: 2,0:02:38.33,0:02:40.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,If building a new settlement on Earth was tough enough,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:40.97,0:02:45.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,那我们完全可以假设到另一个星球殖民更是难上加难
Dialogue: 2,0:02:40.97,0:02:45.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,it's safe to assume that building one on a different planet will be even more difficult.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:46.54,0:02:53.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,为了避免资源上的冲突 殖民者应该会在到达火星前就经济制度达成一致
Dialogue: 2,0:02:46.54,0:02:53.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,To avoid conflicts over resources, the settlers might agree to establish an economy before arriving on Mars.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:53.39,0:02:58.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,经济制度应涉及到当地资源交易内容 或者全新货币的内容
Dialogue: 2,0:02:53.39,0:02:58.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,This economy could be based either on the trade of local resources, or on a brand-new currency,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:59.06,0:03:01.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,这将独立于地球上已有的任何体制
Dialogue: 2,0:02:59.06,0:03:01.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,independent of anything we have here on Earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:02.27,0:03:05.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,为了保证该经济制度的公平合理
Dialogue: 2,0:03:02.27,0:03:05.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,In order for this economy to be fair and balanced,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:05.31,0:03:09.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,还需要一个人或者一个团体来掌管一切
Dialogue: 2,0:03:05.31,0:03:09.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,it will need to be enforced - either by a group or a single person in charge of everything.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:10.18,0:03:13.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,殖民者或许能够从人类在地球上犯下的错误中吸取教训
Dialogue: 2,0:03:10.18,0:03:13.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,Settlers could perhaps learn from the mistakes made on Earth
Dialogue: 1,0:03:13.20,0:03:16.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,制定一个更好的运营城市或国家的体制
Dialogue: 2,0:03:13.20,0:03:16.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,to create a much better system for running a city or country.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:17.00,0:03:24.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,“我认为火星上的政府形式最有可能是直接民主制 而不是代表民主制
Dialogue: 2,0:03:17.00,0:03:24.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,“I think most likely, the form of government on Mars would be a direct democracy, not representative.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:24.73,0:03:28.51,辉中,,0,0,0,,人们可以为某些问题直接投票
Dialogue: 2,0:03:24.73,0:03:28.51,辉英,,0,0,0,,So it would be people voting directly on issues.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:28.66,0:03:35.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,相比于代表民主制 直接民主制潜在的腐败会大幅减少
Dialogue: 2,0:03:28.66,0:03:35.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,The potential for corruption is substantially diminished in a direct verses representative democracy.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:35.44,0:03:39.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,移除一条法律可能比创造一个新的更简单
Dialogue: 2,0:03:35.44,0:03:39.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,It should probably be easier to remove a law than to create one.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:39.66,0:03:45.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,我的建议就是 比如说60%的人同意才能通过某条法律
Dialogue: 2,0:03:39.66,0:03:45.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,My recommendation would be something like let's say - 60% of people need to vote in a law
Dialogue: 1,0:03:45.97,0:03:49.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,但超过40%的人同意就能将其移除
Dialogue: 2,0:03:45.97,0:03:49.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,but at any point greater than 40% people can remove it.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:49.32,0:03:53.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,并且任何法律都应当标明有效期限”
Dialogue: 2,0:03:49.32,0:03:53.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,And any law should come with a built in sunset provision.”
Dialogue: 1,0:03:53.76,0:03:58.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,这样能让法律随着当前文明的进步而发展
Dialogue: 2,0:03:53.76,0:03:58.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,This will help to keep the laws relevant to the current advancement of the civilization.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:58.54,0:04:03.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,5到10年后 火星定居者们可以投票来通过或者废除一条法律
Dialogue: 2,0:03:58.54,0:04:03.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,After 5 or 10 years, the Martians can vote if they want to pass a certain law or get rid of it.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:04.12,0:04:07.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,另一个问题就是潜在的战争威胁
Dialogue: 2,0:04:04.12,0:04:07.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Another problem is the potential threat of war.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.38,0:04:11.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,首批定居者几乎立即回遇到资源极度短缺的情况
Dialogue: 2,0:04:07.38,0:04:11.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,The first settlers could face an extreme shortage of resources almost immediately
Dialogue: 1,0:04:11.90,0:04:15.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果开采水资源的系统与种植系统没有正常运转
Dialogue: 2,0:04:11.90,0:04:15.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,if the systems for mining water and growing food aren't working.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:15.93,0:04:20.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,即使他们有足够的资源 离家遥远所带来的的精神摧残
Dialogue: 2,0:04:15.93,0:04:20.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even if they have enough resources, the mental struggle of being so far from home
Dialogue: 1,0:04:20.54,0:04:25.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,与强制自己适应火星生活的经历也会让一些人濒临崩溃
Dialogue: 2,0:04:20.54,0:04:25.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,and committing to the Martian lifestyle could drive some settlers over the edge.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:26.41,0:04:32.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,当越来越多的殖民者来到火星 他们可能会建立不同的区域 国家甚至大洲
Dialogue: 2,0:04:26.41,0:04:32.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,As soon as more settlers start to arrive on Mars, they might establish different zones, countries or continents.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:33.00,0:04:35.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果没有任何权力来监管这些不同地方的话
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.00,0:04:35.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,And without any authority to police these different places -
Dialogue: 1,0:04:35.90,0:04:40.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,文明之间进步程度的不同可能会带来混乱
Dialogue: 2,0:04:35.90,0:04:40.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,the varying levels of advancement between civilizations could lead to chaos.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:41.62,0:04:46.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些只是要建立永久性殖民地所需要考虑的因素和问题的冰山一角
Dialogue: 2,0:04:41.62,0:04:46.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,These are just a few of the considerations and problems that will need to be addressed
Dialogue: 1,0:04:46.13,0:04:48.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,这些只是要建立永久性殖民地所需要考虑的因素和问题的冰山一角
Dialogue: 2,0:04:46.13,0:04:48.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,if a permanent colony is to be established.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:49.22,0:04:53.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以尽管火星不像是那种能繁衍生息的地方
Dialogue: 2,0:04:49.22,0:04:53.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,So although Mars may not seem like the kind of place to raise your kids,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:54.05,0:04:57.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,但光是想想第一代火星出生的孩子们
Dialogue: 2,0:04:54.05,0:04:57.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,just imagine the first generation of children born on Mars.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:58.18,0:05:00.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,对于他们来说 火星才是故乡
Dialogue: 2,0:04:58.18,0:05:00.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,To them, Mars is home.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:01.08,0:05:06.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们生来就习惯了地下居住舱 沙尘暴 自家种植的食物
Dialogue: 2,0:05:01.08,0:05:06.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,Underground habitats, dust storms and homegrown food is all they are used to.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:06.29,0:05:11.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,对于他们来说 地球只是苍穹中漂浮的一个微小的外星世界罢了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:06.29,0:05:11.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,To them, Earth is just a tiny alien world, floating in the sky.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:11.95,0:05:17.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果你想观看更多殖民火星的内容 请来看看CuriosityStream上这个纪录片
